
Overview of noun devotion

The noun devotion has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (2) devotion, devotedness -- (feelings of ardent love; "their devotion to each other was beautiful")
2. (1) devotion -- (commitment to some purpose; "the devotion of his time and wealth to science")
3. idolatry, devotion, veneration, cultism -- (religious zeal; the willingness to serve God)
4. devotion -- ((usually plural) religious observance or prayers (usually spoken silently); "he returned to his devotions")
